        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>Robert Klonsky, an activist in the Communist Party USA, fought with the Abraham Lincoln Brigade in the Spanish Civil War. The collection includes typed transcripts of 23 letters and postcards written by Klonsky from Spain during the Spanish Civil War, World War II letters; clippings; a flyer for a James Connolly Commoration at Jarama, 1937(photocopy); text of a speech by Klonsky in Leningrad, 1970s; a tribute to Klonsky by Floyce Alexander; documents relating to Klonsky's work in the Communist Party, incoming and copies of outgoing correspondence, including a letter from Ray Bradbury, 1966, one from William O. Douglas, 1963, and a draft of a long letter from Klonsky to Henry Winston; testimony related to HUAC hearings; and Klonsky's speech at his subsequent trial.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <arrangement id="ref33">
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>Files are organized in 1 series: I. General files, 1937-1999.</p>
            <p>Folders are arranged alphabeticqally.</p>
        </arrangement>
